7.00	The_Man_with_One_Red_Shoe	The Man with One Red Shoe	The Man With One Red Shoe is a 1985 comedy film directed by Stan Dragoti. It is a remake of a 1972 French film Le Grand Blond avec une chaussure noire starring Pierre Richard and Mireille Darc. The film included small excerpts from the first three movements of the symphonic suite Scheherazade by Nikolai Rimsky-Korsakov.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e0/Man_with_one_red_shoe_poster.jpg/220px-Man_with_one_red_shoe_poster.jpg
